","1209–Female":"1209–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1205–Male":"1205–Deceased","1230–1315":"1230–1315","1187–Male":"1187–Deceased","1191–Female":"1191–Deceased","1315":"1315","1205":"1205","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","Abt 1209":"about 1209","1209":"1209","1191":"1191","{Blddn ap Cnfn}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italy","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Llewellyn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Welsh: from the personal name <i>Llywelyn</i>, derived from British Celtic <i>Lugubelinos</i>, itself from the divine name <i>Lugus</i> + an uncertain second element often used alone as a name. Through association with <i>llew</i> ‘lion’, it was altered to <i>Llewelyn</i>. This was the name of two princes of north Wales who held the Normans at bay for many years in the 13th century. Etymologically speaking, the form with a fourth <i>-l-</i> is an error, not found as an original Welsh name, but this is now much the most common spelling in the US."]}]},{"name":"Efa","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of several Anglicized forms of the Gaelic name Eithne . In the case of Queen Victoria's granddaughter Princess Ena (Victoria Eugénie Julia Ena,  1887–1969 ) it had a different origin: it was a misreading by the minister who baptized her off a handwritten note of the originally intended name   Eva .  In England, the name is remembered principally as that of the fearsome  Ena Sharples  in the television soap opera Coronation Street.  See also  Ina ."],"variants":[{"name":"Eithne","meanings":["Traditional name, apparently from <i>eithne</i> ‘kernel’, which was used as a term of praise in bardic poetry. St Eithne was a daughter of King Laoghaire and one of St Patrick's first converts."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Efa ferch Llywelyn was born about 1209, in Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Llywelyn ap Cynwrig, was 24 and her mother, Mrs. Llywelyn ap Cynwrig, was 20. She had at least 3 sons with Cynwrig."},"et":{"Abt 1209–Deceased":"umbes 1209–Surnud","1209–Female":"1209–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1230–1315":"1230–1315","1187–Male":"1187–Surnud","1191–Female":"1191–Surnud","1315":"1315","1205":"1205","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","Abt 1209":"umbes 1209","1209":"1209","1191":"1191","{Blddn ap Cnfn}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1209–Deceased":"noin 1209–Kuollut","1209–Female":"1209–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1230–1315":"1230–1315","1187–Male":"1187–Kuollut","1191–Female":"1191–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1205":"1205","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","Abt 1209":"noin 1209","1209":"1209","1191":"1191","{Blddn ap Cnfn}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italia","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1209–Deceased":"environ 1209–Décédée","1209–Female":"1209–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1205–Male":"1205–Décédé","1230–1315":"1230–1315","1187–Male":"1187–Décédé","1191–Female":"1191–Décédée","1315":"1315","1205":"1205","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","Abt 1209":"environ 1209","1209":"1209","1191":"1191","{Blddn ap Cnfn}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italie","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Efa ferch Llywelyn est née environ 1209, à Flintshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, son père, 